title: For Sale:  Vickers Machine Gun Tripod (Colt MFG 1908)
postcontent: I am selling a Vickers machine-gun tripod that was made by Colt in 1904. I suppose it could be used to display a Maxim or a Browning or a Hotchkiss but I am not savvy enough on belt-fed weapons to know this for sure. The tripod itself is quite beautiful, they used a lot of brass when they made things back in the day. Someone has cleaned it up some. This thing made it through two world wars and several dozen smaller conflicts without being scrapped for brass somehow - I guess that makes it kind of special. There does not seem to be a lot of them left in existence. As far as I can tell, the only parts missing are the screws for mounting the data plate to the tripod unit. Might be a good find if you've had a Vickers you've been wanting to complete for display purposes and are squeamish about purchasing a replica or reproduction tripod. Pictures can be made available upon request. Shipping included.
